'''Kume Clan''' (久米氏, くめうじ) is one of the clans of Japan.

== Kume Naoshi ==
{{日本の氏族 (古代氏族)
|氏名 = {{ill|Kume Clan|ja|久米氏}}<br />（{{ill|Kume Naoshi|ja|久米直}}）
|image =
|氏姓 = {{ill|Kume Naoshi|ja|久米直}}
|始祖 = {{ill|Umashimimi no Mikoto|ja|味耳命}} (also known as {{ill|Umashihime no Mikoto|ja|味日命}})
|出自 =
|氏祖 =
|種別 = {{ill|Kamibetsu|ja|神別}}（{{ill|Tenshin|ja|天神}}）
|本貫 =
|人物 =
|後裔 = {{ill|Yamabe Clan|ja|山部氏}}連
}}
In ancient Japan, the Kume Clan was one of the military clans. According to the ''{{ill|Shinsen Seishiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku}}'', they are said to be descendants either of {{ill|Takamikoto no Mikoto|ja|高御魂命}}’s 8th‐generation grandson, {{ill|Umashimimi no Mikoto|ja|味耳命}} (also called {{ill|Umashihime no Mikoto|ja|味日命}}), or of the 8th‐generation grandson of {{ill|Shinkon no Mikoto|ja|神魂命}}. They are associated with the Kumebe (read “くめべ”, sometimes also written as "来目部") clan of the Banzo (【伴造】) type (【久味国造】).

== Kume Omi ==
{{日本の氏族 (古代氏族)
|氏名 = {{ill|Kume Clan|ja|久米氏}}<br />（{{ill|Kume Omi|ja|久米臣}}）
|image =
|氏姓 = {{ill|Kume Omi|ja|久米臣}}
|始祖 =
|出自 = {{ill|Kasuga Clan|ja|春日氏}} (specifically, the branch known as the Wagetsu of the Kasuga line)
|氏祖 =
|種別 = {{ill|Kōbetsu|ja|皇別}}
|本貫 = [[Yamato Province]] [[Takaichi District]] Kume-gō
|人物 =
|後裔 =
}}
The branch known as Kume Omi (久米臣) originated from the Kume-gō of [[Yamato Province]] [[Takaichi District]] and is considered a branch of the Kasuga clan’s Wagetsu lineage.

== Kume Clan of Owari Province ==
{{日本の氏族 (古代氏族)
|氏名 = {{ill|Kume Clan|ja|久米氏}}
|image =
|氏姓 = {{ill|Kume|ja|久米}}
|始祖 = {{ill|Hachimitsu no Mikoto|ja|八甕命}}
|出自 = {{ill|Kume Naoshi|ja|久米直}}
|氏祖 =
