|本貫 = [[Yamato Province]] [[Takaichi District]] Kume-gō
|人物 =
|後裔 =
}}
The Owari branch of the Kume Clan is said to descend from the lineage of {{ill|Hachimitsu no Mikoto|ja|八甕命}}, the descendant of a clan member known as “Shichiku-ketsu,” who is reputed to have served as the chief priest at {{ill|Hijō Shrine|ja|氷上神社}}.

== Kume Clan of Musashi Province ==
{{日本の氏族
|家名 = {{ill|Kume Clan|ja|久米氏}}<br />（武蔵国久米氏）
|家紋 =
|家紋名称 =
|本姓 = {{ill|Heishi|ja|平氏}} (specifically, as a branch of the Kanmu Heishi and the Murayama subgroup)
|家祖 =
