The Musashi branch of the Kume Clan originated from Kume-shō in [[Musashi Province]] [[Iruma District]] and is considered a branch of the Murayama line, which claims descent from the Kanmu Heishi.

== Kume Clan of Hitachi Province ==
{{日本の氏族
|家名 = {{ill|Kume Clan|ja|久米氏|12=draft}}<br />（常陸国久米氏）
|家紋 =
|家紋名称 =
|本姓 = 1. {{ill|Fujiwara Northern Family|ja|藤原北家|12=draft}} (Hidesato lineage, also associated with the Onozaki clan)<br />2. {{ill|Seiwa Genji|ja|清和源氏|12=draft}} (Yoritomo lineage, with a branch related to the Satake clan)
|家祖 = {{ill|Satake Yoshitake|ja|佐竹義武|12=draft}} (Kume Yoshitake)
|種別 = {{ill|Buke|ja|武家|12=draft}}
|出身地 = [[Hitachi Province]] [[Kuzugun]] Kume-gō
|根拠地 = Hitachi Province, Kuzugun, Kume-gō
|人物 =
|支流 =
