|本貫 =
|人物 =
|後裔 = {{ill|Yamabe Clan|ja|山部氏|qq=draft}}連
}}
In ancient Japan, the Kume Clan was one of the military clans. According to the ''{{ill|Shinsen Seishiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=draft}}'', they are said to be descendants either of {{ill|Takamikoto no Mikoto|ja|高御魂命|qq=draft}}’s 8th‐generation grandson, {{ill|Umashimimi no Mikoto|ja|味耳命|qq=draft}} (also called {{ill|Umashihime no Mikoto|ja|味日命|qq=draft}}), or of the 8th‐generation grandson of {{ill|Shinkon no Mikoto|ja|神魂命|qq=draft}}. They are associated with the Kumebe (read “くめべ”, sometimes also written as "来目部") clan of the Banzo (【伴造】) type (【久味国造】).

