The Hitachi branch of the Kume Clan originated from Kume-gō in [[Hitachi Province]]’s [[Kuzugun]] and existed in two major lines—one stemming from the Fujiwara Northern Family (Hidesato/Onozaki lineage) and the other from the Seiwa Genji (Satake lineage). During the Nanboku-chō period, a branch of the clan that sought refuge in Hitachi became indigenous; additionally, during the Sengoku period, members of the Kume clan were said to have been retainers of the Satake clan when it became feudal lords in Hitachi, and many became prosperous farmers in areas corresponding to present-day southern Akita Prefecture (such as Misato Town) and surrounding regions.

