'''Kume Clan''' (久米氏, くめうじ) is one of the clans of Japan.

== Kume Naoshi ==
{{日本の氏族 (古代氏族)
|氏名 = {{ill|Kume Clan|ja|久米氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kume Clan|qq=}}<br />（{{ill|Kume Naoshi|ja|久米直|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kume Naoshi|qq=}}）
|image =
|氏姓 = {{ill|Kume Naoshi|ja|久米直|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kume Naoshi|qq=}}
|始祖 = {{ill|Umashimimi no Mikoto|ja|味耳命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Umashimimi no Mikoto|qq=}} (also known as {{ill|Umashihime no Mikoto|ja|味日命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Umashihime no Mikoto|qq=}})
|出自 =
|氏祖 =
|種別 = {{ill|Kamibetsu|ja|神別|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamibetsu|qq=}}（{{ill|Tenshin|ja|天神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshin|qq=}}）
|本貫 =
|人物 =
|後裔 = {{ill|Yamabe Clan|ja|山部氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamabe Clan|qq=}}連
}}
In ancient Japan, the Kume Clan was one of the military clans. According to the ''{{ill|Shinsen Seishiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinsen Seishiroku|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=}}'', they are said to be descendants either of {{ill|Takamikoto no Mikoto|ja|高御魂命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takamikoto no Mikoto|qq=}}’s 8th‐generation grandson, {{ill|Umashimimi no Mikoto|ja|味耳命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Umashimimi no Mikoto|qq=}} (also called {{ill|Umashihime no Mikoto|ja|味日命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Umashihime no Mikoto|qq=}}), or of the 8th‐generation grandson of {{ill|Shinkon no Mikoto|ja|神魂命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinkon no Mikoto|qq=}}. They are associated with the Kumebe (read “くめべ”, sometimes also written as "来目部") clan of the Banzo (【伴造】) type (【久味国造】).

